protein lenght statistics for E-coli

load Ecoli gene annotation data

Ecoli_genes  <- read.csv("./data/Ecoli_gene_functional_annotations.csv", row.names = 1)
hist(Ecoli_genes$protein_len, col=1, xlab="protein length", main="")
abline(v=mean(Ecoli_genes$protein_len, na.rm=T), col="tomato", lty=2, lwd=2)
abline(v=median(Ecoli_genes$protein_len), col="lightblue", lty=2, lwd=2)
text(1000, 600, paste("average=",round(mean(Ecoli_genes$protein_len))), col="tomato")
text(1000, 500, paste("median=",median(Ecoli_genes$protein_len)), col="lightblue")

Ecoli_genes  <- read.csv("./data/Ecoli_gene_functional_annotations.csv", row.names = 1)

intersect(rownames(Dogma), Ecoli_genes$gene) -> keep

Ecoli_genes <- Ecoli_genes[Ecoli_genes$gene%in%keep,]
Dogma <- Dogma[rownames(Dogma)%in%keep,]

Ecoli_genes <- Ecoli_genes[match(rownames(Dogma), Ecoli_genes$gene),]

par(mar=c(3,20,3,3))
boxplot(log(Dogma$protein.concentration..Pi...1.m3.)~Ecoli_genes$functional_category_desc,las=2, horizontal=T, ylab="")
abline(v=mean(log(Dogma$protein.concentration..Pi...1.m3.), na.rm=T), lwd=2, col=2)
plot(Dogma$mRNA.concentration..mRi...1.m3., Dogma$protein.concentration..Pi...1.m3., log="xy", pch=20)
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
hist(Ecoli_genes$protein_len, xlab="protein length")
abline(v=mean(Ecoli_genes$protein_len), lwd=2, lty=2, col="red")
abline(v=median(Ecoli_genes$protein_len), lwd=2, lty=2, col="blue")
mean(Ecoli_genes$protein_len)
## [1] 355.2991
median(Ecoli_genes$protein_len)
## [1] 310
boxplot(Ecoli_genes$protein_len, xlab="protein length")

L <- split(Ecoli_genes$protein_len, Ecoli_genes$functional_category_desc)
Means <- sapply(L, mean)
par(mar=c(3,20,3,3))
barplot(sort(Means), horiz=T, las=2)

Sds <- sapply(L, sd)

par(mar=c(3,20,3,3))
boxplot(Ecoli_genes$protein_len~factor(Ecoli_genes$functional_category_desc, levels=names(Means)[order(Means)]), las=2, horizontal=T, ylab="")
